    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-12-21T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-12-21T19:00:00-05:00" n="312"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d312">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/595: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia (<persName corresp="#p_CJ1"
                            type="from">Caffery</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-12-21T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 21, 1932—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>86. Department’s 54, December 20, 6 p.m. <persName corresp="#p_OHE1"
                        >Olaya</persName>’s first reaction to <persName corresp="#p_MVM1"
                        >Maúrtua</persName> proposal is favorable although he said that offhand he
                    saw two decided objections: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>The joint commission to go to Leticia should be presided over by an
                            American and,</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>The delay mentioned in the fourth sentence of the Department’s
                            telegram could not be more than 2 weeks as it would be impossible for
                            him to hold up any longer troops now at, and about to arrive at, Para
                            numbering about 2,000 aboard five vessels under command of <persName
                                corresp="#p_VCA2">Vasquez Cobo</persName>.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>The President said he would consult his various official advisers tomorrow
                    morning and give me a definite answer in the afternoon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
